            {
                "s2_paper_id": "c06e339be0c1a087073e10119717e5af1d5d63ef",
                "title": "Defining teacher leadership",
                "year": 2018,
                "venue": "Phi Delta Kappan",
                "citation_count": 37,
                "reference_count": 8,
                "abstract": "Teacher leadership is widely thought to be critical to the success of local school improvement efforts. But it\u2019s often unclear what teacher leadership entails, precisely. Supported by district-level staff, and with assistance from a university-based research team (the authors of this article), a group of science teacher leaders created a conceptual framework to guide their work. Teacher leadership, they concluded, involves four main activities: collaborating with teachers, modeling effective instruction, providing resources, and advocating on teachers\u2019 behalf.",
